 1.😜 Threads in operating system || Single and Multi-threaded processes || Benefits

     🧠 Threads in Operating System
         A thread is the smallest unit of execution inside a process.
         👉 A process can have multiple threads sharing the same memory.

     🧠 Single vs Multi-threaded Process
        🔹 Single-threaded
        Only one thread executes
        One task at a time
        
        👉 Example: simple program  

       🔹 Multi-threaded
            Multiple threads in one process
            Multiple tasks run concurrently
            
            👉 Example: web browser (tabs, downloads)

     🧠 Benefits of Multithreading
          Faster execution (parallelism)
          Better CPU utilization
          Responsiveness (UI doesn’t freeze)
          Resource sharing (same memory)    



 2.😣  Multi-threading Models in operating system || Many to one || Many to many || one to one

           Multithreading models define how user threads are mapped to kernel threads.

          1. Many-to-One Model
             Many user threads → one kernel thread
             Managed in user space
             
             👉 ❌ If one thread blocks → all block
             👉 ❌ No true parallelism  

          2. One-to-One Model
            Each user thread → one kernel thread
            
            👉 ✅ True parallelism
            👉 ❌ High overhead (more resources) 

          3. Many-to-Many Model
             Many user threads → many kernel threads
             
             👉 ✅ Flexible & efficient
             👉 ✅ Allows parallelism without too much overhead             
                                                 
  3.🤒  Threading Issues In Operating Systems  

          Threading issues are problems that arise when multiple threads execute concurrently.   

          1. Race Condition
              Multiple threads access shared data simultaneously
              Leads to incorrect results 

          2. Deadlock
             Threads wait for each other forever
             No progress  

         3. Starvation
            A thread never gets CPU/resources
            Keeps waiting indefinitely    

         4. Thread Synchronization
            Need mechanisms like mutex, semaphore
            Ensures correct execution  

         5. Context Switching Overhead
             Switching between threads takes time
             Affects performance    